-- Uzumeri Leaves Ontario Teachers' to Start Own Management Firm, Globe Says
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-04-23T12:39:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/uzumeri-leaves-ontario-teachers-to-start-own-management-firm-globe-says.html

          
          
             Erol Uzumeri left his post as head
of private equity at Ontario Teachersâ€™ Pension Plan this week to
start his own money-management firm, the Globe and Mail reported
in its Streetwise column, citing unidentified people.  
 Uzumeri, 40, ran a C$10 billion ($9.97 billion) arm of the
pension fund, the newspaper said. He declined to tell the
newspaper about plans to start his own company.  
